U.K. Public Servants Face Pension Contribution Increase, FT Says

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 
2011-07-20T01:51:12Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-20/u-k-public-servants-face-pension-contribution-increase-ft-says.html
High-paid U.K. public servants,
including National Health Service doctors, head teachers and
senior police figures will see an increase in their pension
contributions of 6 percentage points, and in some cases close to
double, the Financial Times reported citing Chief Treasury
Secretary Danny Alexander.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blanche Gatt in London at 
 bgatt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 